Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Mince @garlic{2%clove}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @yogurt{2%ounce}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, half the garlic, @shawarma spice blend{1%tsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @pepper{}. Add @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} and turn to coat. Set aside to marinate for ~{15%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil, 2 tsp Shawarma Spice, and 2 tsp salt.

While chicken marinates, halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP (¼ cup for 4 servings). Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}; pat very dry with #paper towels{}. Chop @cilantro{¼%ounce} leaves and stems. Roughly chop @pistachios{1%ounce}.

Toss onion wedges, chickpeas, and @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tablespoon}, @shawarma spice{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper. Roast, tossing halfway through, until chickpeas are crispy and veggies are tender, about ~{20%minutes}.

> For 4, divide between 2 baking sheets; swap rack positions halfway through roasting.

> TIP: It's natural for some chickpeas to pop as they roast.

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @dried cherries{1%ounce}, minced onion, half the pistachios, remaining Shawarma Spice, and a @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, for ~{1%minute}. Stir in @basmati rice{½%cup}, @water{¾%cup}, and a large pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium heat. Remove chicken from marinade; allow excess to drip off. Add chicken to pan and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle, slice chicken crosswise.

> TIP: Medium heat is key in preventing the marinade from burning. If chicken begins to brown too quickly, lower the heat.

== White Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and remaining garlic to taste. Stir in @water{}, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}, half the cilantro, salt, and pepper. Divide rice between plates; top with chicken and veggies. Drizzle with sauce; top with remaining pistachios and cilantro.